1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:05,633
A surgeon must make calm decisions
and achieve swift hemostasis.

2
00:00:06,966 --> 00:00:13,710
Incidentally, I first experienced this
in the spring of my second year here.

3
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:18,763
This would later be known
as the Miracle of Taishaku.

4
00:00:18,809 --> 00:00:20,019
Wait...

5
00:00:20,303 --> 00:00:22,860
When will he even get to the main point?

6
00:00:23,046 --> 00:00:24,929
- Morning!
- Good morning.

7
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:27,290
Studying this early? Good for you.

8
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:29,189
My Surgery rotation starts tomorrow.

9
00:00:29,283 --> 00:00:31,926
Dr. Kongo made me buy this
and told me to read it.

10
00:00:31,926 --> 00:00:34,218
So your time
at the Emergency Department is over, then.

11
00:00:34,218 --> 00:00:35,422
Yes.

12
00:00:35,519 --> 00:00:37,233
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

13
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:39,887
Anno, it's time to say goodbye to Yakushiji.

14
00:00:39,887 --> 00:00:40,980
Hmm.

15
00:00:40,980 --> 00:00:43,350
She doesn't seem the least bit sorry
to see me go.

16
00:00:44,549 --> 00:00:48,973
Hey, Anno! That's the pudding
I bought. Give it back.

17
00:00:49,582 --> 00:00:51,136
Buy your own...

18
00:00:51,953 --> 00:00:53,283
What was that?

19
00:00:56,699 --> 00:00:57,906
Huh?

20
00:01:00,319 --> 00:01:01,599
Incoming.

21
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:04,716
On three. One, two, three!

22
00:01:07,159 --> 00:01:08,792
Where am I?

23
00:01:09,925 --> 00:01:11,492
Who the hell are you?!

24
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,826
He's agitated!

25
00:01:12,826 --> 00:01:16,013
Please calm down! You're in a hospital!

26
00:01:16,013 --> 00:01:17,169
Don't touch me!

27
00:01:17,169 --> 00:01:19,059
- Starting an IV.
- Let me go home!

28
00:01:24,806 --> 00:01:26,100
Are you okay?

29
00:01:39,290 --> 00:01:40,496
Anno!

30
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,400
Dr. Anno! Are you all right?

31
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,460
Get a line in and give him a sedative. Now.

32
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:47,240
But you're bleeding...

33
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,896
The patient comes first. Hurry!

34
00:01:48,896 --> 00:01:50,060
Yes!

35
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,653
Yakushiji, prep the line!

36
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:52,766
Okay.

37
00:01:52,766 --> 00:01:54,393
- I'll get the sedative.
- Yes.

38
00:01:59,976 --> 00:02:04,250
Well, there's swelling from the bruise,
but no other notable findings.

39
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:06,310
Told you it was nothing.

40
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:08,250
Still, take it easy.

41
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:11,190
We're short-staffed. I can't sit out
over a minor injury like this.

42
00:02:11,430 --> 00:02:12,903
It's a big help for sure.

43
00:02:12,903 --> 00:02:14,050
But hey,

44
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:16,483
at least finish eating it.

45
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:21,010
Today's your last night shift in the ER, huh?

46
00:02:21,103 --> 00:02:24,396
Yeah. When I'd first heard
that an Ashura lives in the ER,

47
00:02:24,775 --> 00:02:28,068
I never imagined she'd be this intense.

48
00:02:29,395 --> 00:02:30,688
Dr. Anno!

49
00:02:30,688 --> 00:02:31,890
Incoming.

50
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:43,250
Let's begin. Scalpel.

51
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:44,450
Here.

52
00:03:10,576 --> 00:03:12,023
Dr. Anno!

53
00:03:13,802 --> 00:03:15,515
Your position is off.

54
00:03:19,476 --> 00:03:20,803
What's wrong?

55
00:03:22,096 --> 00:03:23,563
Just a slight slip of the hand.

56
00:03:37,796 --> 00:03:39,030
- Retractor.
- Got it.

57
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:40,636
There's so much bleeding!

58
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,110
It's arterial bleeding!

59
00:03:43,110 --> 00:03:44,309
Suction.

60
00:03:44,309 --> 00:03:45,575
Okay.

61
00:03:47,709 --> 00:03:49,169
- Towel.
- Here.

62
00:03:51,203 --> 00:03:53,696
I can't find the bleeding point.

63
00:03:54,383 --> 00:03:57,496
I'll trace along the artery
to find the source.

64
00:04:07,313 --> 00:04:10,550
Found it. Z-suture ligation for hemostasis.

65
00:04:10,622 --> 00:04:11,805
Black silk, 3-0.

66
00:04:11,805 --> 00:04:13,006
Here!

67
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:35,263
Thank you for everything
these past three months.

68
00:04:35,306 --> 00:04:37,960
We'll be waiting for you
to come back to the ER.

69
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:42,216
But I have to go into dermatology
and take over my family's practice.

70
00:04:42,709 --> 00:04:46,186
Emergency! A patient in the ICU has
taken a sudden turn for the worse!

71
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:55,676
Blood pressure suddenly dropped to the 70s.

72
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:58,636
Massive bleeding from the drain.

73
00:04:58,650 --> 00:05:00,723
Likely postoperative rebleeding.

74
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:02,910
Anno, we're operating immediately.

75
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,183
Anno, what's wrong?

76
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:12,170
I can't operate.

77
00:05:12,699 --> 00:05:13,900
What?

78
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:17,763
My eyes...

79
00:05:19,830 --> 00:05:21,383
I can't see well.

80
00:05:25,059 --> 00:05:26,340
BP's in the 50s.

81
00:05:26,340 --> 00:05:29,663
No time. I'll operate.
Get everything ready now.

82
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:30,916
Understood.

83
00:05:34,896 --> 00:05:36,423
Where was...

84
00:05:37,089 --> 00:05:38,770
the source of the bleeding?

85
00:05:45,973 --> 00:05:47,236
Last night,

86
00:05:47,829 --> 00:05:51,263
the bleeding came from where you performed
the ligation sutures.

87
00:05:58,156 --> 00:05:59,776
Postoperative bleeding can

88
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:04,970
occur as a complication even
when nothing went wrong in the surgery.

89
00:06:05,370 --> 00:06:08,750
It's not necessarily your fault, Anno.

90
00:06:10,354 --> 00:06:11,563
But...

91
00:06:13,322 --> 00:06:15,676
This has never happened before.

92
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:20,923
I'm so sorry.

93
00:06:26,476 --> 00:06:27,696
How are your eyes?

94
00:06:32,310 --> 00:06:35,123
There were no issues at yesterday's exam...

95
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:39,483
Anyway, let's run another exam.

96
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:48,273
It looks like there are fractures
in the right orbital floor and optic canal.

97
00:06:48,273 --> 00:06:56,273
That's causing diplopia when looking down
and vision loss from optic nerve compression.

98
00:06:57,220 --> 00:07:02,296
The swelling must have
hidden the fracture lines on the initial CT.

99
00:07:03,906 --> 00:07:09,510
This falls under plastic surgery.
Dr. Rikudo, what's your assessment?

100
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:16,330
If the optic nerve keeps swelling
and compression worsens, vision will decline.

101
00:07:17,613 --> 00:07:21,696
The only cure is
optic nerve decompression surgery.

102
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,739
However,

103
00:07:25,552 --> 00:07:30,430
this surgery needs to be performed
within the next few days.

104
00:07:30,582 --> 00:07:34,096
If not, the chances of recovery drop
significantly even with surgery.

105
00:07:35,346 --> 00:07:39,446
Dr. Naomi, let's start
preparing for surgery right away.

106
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:45,906
This procedure is extremely difficult,
and there are very few documented cases.

107
00:07:47,126 --> 00:07:49,646
I don't even know
the detailed surgical approach,

108
00:07:51,185 --> 00:07:53,193
so I can't perform it.

109
00:07:54,107 --> 00:07:55,232
What?

110
00:07:55,232 --> 00:07:57,698
Very few surgeons can perform this operation.

111
00:07:59,018 --> 00:08:01,272
Whether we can find one quickly...

112
00:08:02,925 --> 00:08:04,873
I honestly don't know.

113
00:08:11,836 --> 00:08:15,309
Dr. Ashura

114
00:08:23,709 --> 00:08:26,462
Dr. Ashura, how are you feeling?

115
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:34,890
How many times now? Ashura just ignores me.
No matter, onward!

116
00:08:35,470 --> 00:08:40,830
I must say, I never expected Dr. Ashura
to be admitted here as a patient!

117
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:47,730
The chairwoman and the director are
searching for a surgeon to operate.

118
00:08:48,398 --> 00:08:51,910
I've become head of the clinical department,
but I still serve as chief of surgery.

119
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:55,823
So, in the meantime,
leave yourself to me, Matayoshi Kongo!

120
00:08:57,036 --> 00:08:58,323
Also...

121
00:08:59,215 --> 00:09:03,530
I've assigned Dr. Yakushiji
as your attending physician.

122
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:12,343
Dr. Yakushiji, I'm in your hands.

123
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:16,763
I will do my best.

124
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:20,426
First, let me draw some blood.

125
00:09:23,890 --> 00:09:28,116
It'll be quite a sight to see
how the ER manages without Ashura.

126
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:33,663
Then again, if they make mistakes, it falls
on me as head of the clinical department.

127
00:09:33,663 --> 00:09:37,376
I absolutely cannot have that!
Absolutely not!

128
00:09:37,430 --> 00:09:39,150
I must warn them...

129
00:09:41,090 --> 00:09:43,430
Was I talking to myself just now?

130
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:48,236
I must be tired.

131
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:13,670
Director Tamon and I searched all day, but...

132
00:10:15,473 --> 00:10:18,330
We couldn't find a surgeon
to perform the operation.

133
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,636
There's still time.

134
00:10:25,676 --> 00:10:27,476
We'll find someone no matter what.

135
00:10:30,723 --> 00:10:32,343
It's all right.

136
00:10:33,109 --> 00:10:35,042
We'll find someone in time.

137
00:10:39,089 --> 00:10:41,535
Without me, the ER falls apart.

138
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:48,696
Lives we could have saved
might slip through the cracks.

139
00:10:57,904 --> 00:10:59,556
You don't need to carry

140
00:11:00,872 --> 00:11:03,500
all that burden alone.

141
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:09,070
The Emergency Department has
other excellent doctors, too.

142
00:11:11,340 --> 00:11:13,710
Even if you rest a little,

143
00:11:14,179 --> 00:11:15,843
it'll be fine.

144
00:11:24,298 --> 00:11:27,333
Male, twenties. Abdominal trauma
from a traffic accident.

145
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:29,093
We can accept. Bring him in.

146
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:32,860
Likely an emergency operation.
Is an OR available?

147
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:38,610
Well, thanks to Surgery, the ORs are
running at full capacity. None free.

148
00:11:38,610 --> 00:11:42,463
As always, it's we in Surgery
who keep Taishaku running.

149
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:46,043
Dr. Yakushiji, if you'd like to join...

150
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:48,482
Oh, you can't.

151
00:11:48,775 --> 00:11:53,106
You're taking over your family's
dermatology practice, aren't you?

152
00:11:55,673 --> 00:11:57,043
Don't tell me...

153
00:11:58,173 --> 00:12:00,063
You want to join the Emergency Department.

154
00:12:00,293 --> 00:12:04,823
Of course not. Being an ER doctor is
not really something to aspire to.

155
00:12:05,016 --> 00:12:06,229
Incoming!

156
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,823
It actually came!

157
00:12:10,325 --> 00:12:12,168
Yes, what happened?

158
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,320
- Scalpel.
- Here.

159
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,963
Heavy bleeding.

160
00:12:19,086 --> 00:12:20,589
- Suction.
- Okay.

161
00:12:24,183 --> 00:12:25,386
There it is.

162
00:12:26,002 --> 00:12:27,628
- Large gauze.
- Here.

163
00:12:28,029 --> 00:12:29,670
Applying pressure to the bleed.

164
00:12:39,956 --> 00:12:42,256
Something's wrong.
There's something in the blood.

165
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:46,470
This is bad. This isn't bleeding.

166
00:12:46,863 --> 00:12:49,663
- What?
- The bowel's ruptured and leaking contents.

167
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:53,843
Could it be an intestinal perforation?

168
00:12:55,055 --> 00:12:56,529
BP's in the 50s.

169
00:12:56,536 --> 00:12:58,049
He's in septic shock.

170
00:12:58,049 --> 00:12:59,676
Crush damage too severe to suture.

171
00:12:59,676 --> 00:13:01,270
His heart will stop at this rate.

172
00:13:01,270 --> 00:13:04,390
This is beyond us.
Let's hand it off to Surgery.

173
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:07,190
The surgeons are in the OR.
They can't come right away.

174
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:22,990
Everyone.

175
00:13:24,522 --> 00:13:30,583
I heard that the ER called. I came to check
because I had a bad feeling, and sure enough.

176
00:13:31,126 --> 00:13:32,936
Utterly pathetic.

177
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:38,023
You there, nurse! Bring this Matayoshi Kongo
a gown and gloves at once.

178
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,533
Got it.

179
00:13:53,222 --> 00:13:56,616
Thanks to you,
we were able to save the patient.

180
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:59,222
Thank you so much. It was a huge help.

181
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:01,243
Think nothing of it. Child's play.

182
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:06,963
As I'd suspected, the ER simply falls apart
without Ashura, doesn't it?

183
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:11,890
Well, it was never more
than a ragtag bunch to begin with.

184
00:14:12,149 --> 00:14:15,330
At the very least,
try not to drag Surgery down with you.

185
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:22,636
Dr. Bonten, how old is your little one now?

186
00:14:22,970 --> 00:14:26,016
Oh, not even one year old yet.

187
00:14:26,963 --> 00:14:28,676
Ah, not even one year old yet.

188
00:14:38,493 --> 00:14:42,639
So that happened in the ER.
Well, in any case...

189
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:44,825
I'm glad the patient pulled
through all right.

190
00:14:44,825 --> 00:14:46,050
Yes.

191
00:14:46,725 --> 00:14:52,032
But there's no guarantee we can
save them next time.

192
00:14:54,283 --> 00:14:55,511
So...

193
00:14:55,949 --> 00:14:58,716
I actually have a favor to ask.

194
00:15:35,683 --> 00:15:36,950
What is it?

195
00:15:42,973 --> 00:15:49,856
Until you're back, the ER will
temporarily stop accepting critical patients.

196
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:52,416
Why?

197
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:55,090
We decided after discussing it
with Dr. Daikoku.

198
00:15:56,056 --> 00:15:57,276
But...

199
00:15:57,836 --> 00:16:01,756
Then we won't be able to save lives
that could've been saved.

200
00:16:02,586 --> 00:16:07,289
But as things stand, the ER can't
provide adequate care even if we accept them.

201
00:16:12,766 --> 00:16:14,099
I'm sorry.

202
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:18,593
If only this hadn't happened to me.

203
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:45,450
Oh, hello?

204
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:49,603
Dr. Naomi is off today, isn't she?

205
00:16:49,869 --> 00:16:51,762
Something urgent came up, apparently.

206
00:16:51,983 --> 00:16:56,603
With Dr. Anno gone too,
I just hope nothing happens.

207
00:16:56,949 --> 00:16:59,569
All we can do is pray for a quiet day.

208
00:16:59,816 --> 00:17:00,850
Right.

209
00:17:00,850 --> 00:17:04,690
I brought this
from the break room like you asked.

210
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:06,623
Thank you, Dr. Yakushiji.

211
00:17:07,329 --> 00:17:09,636
Give this My Number Card to the admin staff.

212
00:17:09,636 --> 00:17:11,423
Oh, sure.

213
00:17:11,956 --> 00:17:13,195
Also...

214
00:17:13,621 --> 00:17:15,669
Here, you should have this, too.

215
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:26,363
I thought it might serve
as a good luck charm.

216
00:17:29,066 --> 00:17:33,270
If there's anything else you need,
just let me know.

217
00:17:41,573 --> 00:17:42,930
Dr. Yakushiji.

218
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:47,129
Could you take these documents
to Gunma Medical Center?

219
00:17:47,129 --> 00:17:48,885
- Yes, sir.
- Mailing it would be too slow.

220
00:17:48,885 --> 00:17:51,729
- Right. Understood.
- Take the hospital car.

221
00:17:51,763 --> 00:17:53,830
- Yes, sir.
- Hurry now.

222
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,343
Oh, Dr. Yakushiji.

223
00:17:56,669 --> 00:18:00,213
I certainly don't need any sweet souvenirs.

224
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,495
Right.

225
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:06,943
Yaki manju! No, wait. I mean, see you later.

226
00:18:24,628 --> 00:18:25,828
Incoming.

227
00:18:34,183 --> 00:18:35,210
Yes.

228
00:18:35,210 --> 00:18:40,883
Multi-vehicle highway accident, six injured.
Two red, three green, one still trapped.

229
00:18:40,883 --> 00:18:42,103
Six patients.

230
00:18:45,835 --> 00:18:48,896
I'm sorry, but right now...

231
00:18:49,135 --> 00:18:52,550
we can't take critical patients.

232
00:18:53,415 --> 00:18:57,883
We placed the others, but we can't find
a hospital to take these six.

233
00:18:57,916 --> 00:18:59,540
Please, can you help us?

234
00:19:10,693 --> 00:19:12,136
I'll help, too.

235
00:19:15,325 --> 00:19:16,700
Accept them.

236
00:19:28,383 --> 00:19:29,823
Right.

237
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:36,663
Understood. Bring in all six.

238
00:19:37,212 --> 00:19:38,977
Dr. Daikoku, it's Kichijoji.

239
00:19:39,349 --> 00:19:40,690
One of the patients is...

240
00:19:41,109 --> 00:19:42,428
Dr. Yakushiji.

241
00:19:50,910 --> 00:19:53,430
Understood. Please proceed.

242
00:19:58,126 --> 00:20:00,043
Prepare for incoming patients.

243
00:20:00,172 --> 00:20:01,372
Got it!

244
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:08,076
Don't push yourself. Just do what you can.

245
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:10,000
Got it.

246
00:20:11,133 --> 00:20:12,671
Center bed, please.

247
00:20:12,671 --> 00:20:14,905
On three. One, two, three.

248
00:20:15,366 --> 00:20:16,819
Prep the patient.

249
00:20:17,281 --> 00:20:18,306
Can you hear me?

250
00:20:18,306 --> 00:20:19,929
- One, two, three.
- Touching your feet.

251
00:20:19,929 --> 00:20:21,535
- Prep the patient.
- Got it.

252
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:25,146
- More coming.
- Can you understand me?

253
00:20:25,252 --> 00:20:28,502
Anno. Go and handle Yakushiji.

254
00:20:28,502 --> 00:20:29,712
Got it.

255
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,460
Dr. Yakushiji, you okay?

256
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:33,790
Dr. Anno.

257
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:36,146
I'm sorry.

258
00:20:36,146 --> 00:20:38,920
- He is alert. Suspected right leg fracture.
- Got it.

259
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,236
Stretcher coming in.

260
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,530
- Prep the patient.
- Yes.

261
00:20:44,553 --> 00:20:45,929
All yours.

262
00:20:49,643 --> 00:20:51,083
I'm going to touch you.

263
00:20:54,850 --> 00:20:58,290
Suspected intestinal rupture.
We need an exploratory laparotomy now.

264
00:20:58,290 --> 00:21:02,123
This one's got intra-abdominal bleeding, too.
We need to open up and stop it immediately.

265
00:21:02,123 --> 00:21:04,190
Doctor, we've secured two operating rooms.

266
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:08,016
But with this staff, we can't run
two emergency surgeries at once.

267
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:09,696
One of them will have to wait.

268
00:21:09,710 --> 00:21:12,510
But both patients are critical.
Every second counts.

269
00:21:12,510 --> 00:21:14,896
At this rate, we'll lose one of them.

270
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:38,203
Director Tamon.

271
00:21:38,303 --> 00:21:39,576
Status?

272
00:21:39,996 --> 00:21:43,629
Two patients need emergency surgery.
We don't have enough staff.

273
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,436
I'll operate on this one alone.

274
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,773
You can't operate solo!

275
00:21:53,773 --> 00:21:54,983
I'll manage.

276
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,196
Get this patient to the OR now.

277
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,463
Yes!

278
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:01,323
Anno, stay here with the head nurse
and continue treatment.

279
00:22:01,549 --> 00:22:02,796
Got it.

280
00:22:22,497 --> 00:22:23,983
Hurry up!

281
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:27,496
We'll treat you right away.
Just hold on a little longer.

282
00:22:27,496 --> 00:22:28,810
It hurts!

283
00:22:45,149 --> 00:22:46,629
It hurts!

284
00:22:46,730 --> 00:22:48,683
Let me help, too.

285
00:22:48,683 --> 00:22:49,710
Dr. Yakushiji!

286
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:51,710
What are you saying? Wait for treatment.

287
00:22:53,176 --> 00:22:54,416
I'm fine.

288
00:22:57,329 --> 00:22:59,223
I'll give you pain meds right away.

289
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:14,350
BP's 74 over 40. It keeps dropping.

290
00:23:16,010 --> 00:23:18,716
Dr. Tamon, the bleeding won't stop.

291
00:23:24,886 --> 00:23:28,876
Found it. It's bleeding
from the hepatic artery.

292
00:23:29,220 --> 00:23:31,486
- Clamping it. Occlusion forceps.
- Here.

293
00:23:40,426 --> 00:23:42,342
Bleeding has stopped.

294
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:51,170
Doctor, there's bleeding elsewhere.
BP's in the 40s.

295
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:55,703
Splenic rupture. Clamping the hepatic
artery raised pressure on the spleen.

296
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:58,630
Not just the liver, but the spleen too...

297
00:23:58,879 --> 00:24:01,132
- I'll call Surgery for backup.
- No need.

298
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:04,652
I'll do both sites simultaneously.

299
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:12,436
The bowel is crushed.
We can't suture it as is.

300
00:24:12,583 --> 00:24:15,716
We need to resect the necrotic tissue
and perform anastomosis.

301
00:24:22,226 --> 00:24:23,442
Dr. Bonten.

302
00:24:25,930 --> 00:24:30,230
It's the exact same condition
as the previous patient.

303
00:24:30,256 --> 00:24:31,969
Crush damage too severe to suture.

304
00:24:31,969 --> 00:24:35,243
This is beyond us.
Let's hand it off to Surgery.

305
00:24:39,743 --> 00:24:41,483
BP is 60 over 32.

306
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:45,463
Septic shock.
The patient will go into cardiac arrest.

307
00:24:45,463 --> 00:24:48,950
Dr. Bonten, we can't perform
this operation right now.

308
00:24:49,050 --> 00:24:51,849
Let's just irrigate and do
a temporary abdominal closure.

309
00:24:53,990 --> 00:24:55,356
Dr. Bonten!

310
00:25:05,109 --> 00:25:07,990
All patients have been handed off to Surgery.

311
00:25:08,556 --> 00:25:09,829
Thank goodness.

312
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:12,750
It's really all thanks to you.

313
00:25:13,049 --> 00:25:14,249
No...

314
00:25:14,770 --> 00:25:17,690
Now it's your turn, Dr. Yakushiji.

315
00:25:18,650 --> 00:25:19,862
Yes.

316
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,066
What?

317
00:25:33,373 --> 00:25:34,751
- Dr. Yakushiji!
- On his back.

318
00:25:34,751 --> 00:25:35,899
Yes.

319
00:25:35,899 --> 00:25:36,953
Can you hear me?

320
00:25:36,953 --> 00:25:38,466
- Check vitals.
- Okay.

321
00:25:38,466 --> 00:25:40,806
Can you hear me? Dr. Yakushiji!

322
00:25:41,420 --> 00:25:42,820
Dr. Yakushiji!

323
00:25:43,447 --> 00:25:45,093
Dr. Yakushiji!

324
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:49,953
Ginza-exclusive limited pudding,
how do you do?

325
00:25:50,513 --> 00:25:51,973
We finally meet.

326
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,563
Worth the 90-minute wait in line.

327
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:57,543
I'm moved. Time to dig in.

328
00:26:04,289 --> 00:26:05,489
Yes?

329
00:26:05,976 --> 00:26:07,722
Gunma Medical Center.

330
00:26:08,250 --> 00:26:10,210
Thank you for your continued support.

331
00:26:10,309 --> 00:26:11,509
Yes.

332
00:26:12,248 --> 00:26:15,002
Yakushiji hasn't arrived yet.

333
00:26:15,243 --> 00:26:16,476
What?

334
00:26:16,663 --> 00:26:18,750
He should've been there by now.

335
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:20,770
I'm terribly sorry.

336
00:26:20,802 --> 00:26:23,876
I'll look into it right away. Yes. Goodbye.

337
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:29,600
Dr. Yakushiji,
where on earth are you dawdling?

338
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:32,043
Don't tell me...

339
00:26:32,740 --> 00:26:34,670
Buying sweet souvenirs?

340
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,216
Let me eat my pudding first.

341
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,123
Dr. Kongo!

342
00:26:43,267 --> 00:26:44,770
Now what?!

343
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:46,276
What are they doing?!

344
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:51,690
Dr. Daikoku and that Normal Hand can't
handle emergency surgery!

345
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,846
Damn it!

346
00:26:57,100 --> 00:26:59,160
Don't act without my approval!

347
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:04,440
If you two make a mistake,
it's me, the Head of Surgery, who...

348
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:07,150
Huh?

349
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:14,863
Resection of necrotic tissue is complete.

350
00:27:16,873 --> 00:27:18,963
Ready for anastomosis.

351
00:27:20,475 --> 00:27:21,526
- Forceps.
- Here.

352
00:27:21,526 --> 00:27:23,553
- Black silk, 3-0.
- Here.

353
00:27:29,620 --> 00:27:32,200
Why is Dr. Bonten performing this operation?

354
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:37,386
After the last surgery, he and Dr. Rikudo ran
simulations together repeatedly.

355
00:27:38,656 --> 00:27:39,856
What?

356
00:27:48,706 --> 00:27:50,076
Impressive.

357
00:27:51,333 --> 00:27:52,460
God Hand.

358
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:55,540
Dr. Kongo, prepare an Endo GIA Green.

359
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:57,110
Yes, understood!

360
00:28:02,070 --> 00:28:03,456
Ready when you are.

361
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:07,216
Massive bleeding in the abdomen.

362
00:28:08,090 --> 00:28:12,570
Bleeding progressed from the injury site
and caused hemorrhagic shock.

363
00:28:14,710 --> 00:28:18,470
We need to open him up and stop
the bleeding now, or we'll lose him.

364
00:28:18,976 --> 00:28:22,950
But the other doctors haven't returned yet.

365
00:28:28,690 --> 00:28:29,989
I'll do it.

366
00:28:30,930 --> 00:28:32,170
But...

367
00:28:34,070 --> 00:28:37,290
If I open and clamp the vessel,
it'll hold for 30 minutes.

368
00:28:37,783 --> 00:28:40,290
If another doctor returns by then,
we can save him.

369
00:28:43,165 --> 00:28:44,636
Prep now. Hurry.

370
00:28:46,603 --> 00:28:47,803
Understood.

371
00:29:33,060 --> 00:29:34,920
Blood pressure keeps dropping.

372
00:30:15,608 --> 00:30:16,810
Found it.

373
00:30:32,465 --> 00:30:33,816
Thank goodness.

374
00:30:35,890 --> 00:30:37,349
The bleeding has stopped.

375
00:30:41,905 --> 00:30:44,210
- Asystole.
- Prepare adrenaline.

376
00:30:44,210 --> 00:30:45,416
Got it.

377
00:30:52,370 --> 00:30:54,235
Dissecting the spleen. Kelly forceps.

378
00:30:54,235 --> 00:30:55,448
Got it.

379
00:31:01,863 --> 00:31:04,003
- Cooper scissors.
- Yes...

380
00:31:05,110 --> 00:31:07,250
Doctor, it's bleeding again.

381
00:31:07,250 --> 00:31:09,089
Bleeding from the liver surface.

382
00:31:09,103 --> 00:31:10,509
- Needle holder.
- Got it.

383
00:31:12,190 --> 00:31:14,389
Sorry, I'll get a new one right away.

384
00:31:14,389 --> 00:31:15,596
Suture needle.

385
00:31:15,710 --> 00:31:17,770
What? A suture needle?

386
00:31:33,819 --> 00:31:35,172
You're suturing by hand?

387
00:31:35,380 --> 00:31:38,192
For surface bleeding,
hand suturing is faster.

388
00:31:48,956 --> 00:31:50,240
Cooper scissors.

389
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,456
Here.

390
00:31:53,380 --> 00:31:55,570
Good. Back to the spleen.

391
00:31:55,756 --> 00:31:56,963
Yes.

392
00:32:07,286 --> 00:32:08,596
Amazing.

393
00:32:08,940 --> 00:32:10,423
All by himself,

394
00:32:10,726 --> 00:32:12,966
the spleen and liver at the same time.

395
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:21,260
Dr. Yakushiji,

396
00:32:21,336 --> 00:32:22,696
hang in there.

397
00:32:24,306 --> 00:32:26,083
You can't die!

398
00:32:27,020 --> 00:32:28,760
You have to keep living.

399
00:32:34,317 --> 00:32:35,576
Dr. Anno...

400
00:32:37,743 --> 00:32:39,963
It's been over 20 minutes.

401
00:32:57,603 --> 00:32:59,163
Doctor.

402
00:33:06,990 --> 00:33:08,810
You're a doctor!

403
00:33:11,109 --> 00:33:13,896
You're going to save so many lives!

404
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:17,750
You can't die here!

405
00:33:19,850 --> 00:33:21,470
Come back!

406
00:33:22,129 --> 00:33:23,636
Kid!

407
00:33:59,053 --> 00:34:00,256
He's back.

408
00:34:06,527 --> 00:34:08,690
Cardiopulmonary function restored.

409
00:34:13,950 --> 00:34:16,160
It's been 25 minutes since clamping.

410
00:34:19,053 --> 00:34:20,923
Only five minutes left.

411
00:34:59,460 --> 00:35:00,905
Dr. Anno.

412
00:35:00,905 --> 00:35:02,310
There's no time left.

413
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,900
I have to do it myself.

414
00:35:44,506 --> 00:35:45,723
Wait!

415
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:19,123
Dr. Naomi.

416
00:36:25,483 --> 00:36:26,883
Dr. Ashura.

417
00:36:27,610 --> 00:36:29,596
You held on until now.

418
00:36:30,823 --> 00:36:32,176
Leave the rest to me.

419
00:36:34,730 --> 00:36:35,930
Please.

420
00:36:37,290 --> 00:36:38,496
Status?

421
00:36:38,750 --> 00:36:41,343
Five minutes to release the clamp,
or we lose him.

422
00:36:41,362 --> 00:36:42,570
Understood.

423
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:44,963
I'll suture the bleeding site right away.

424
00:37:48,976 --> 00:37:50,309
Anno.

425
00:37:50,570 --> 00:37:51,843
Thank you.

426
00:37:52,990 --> 00:37:56,510
Because you said we should accept them,

427
00:37:56,890 --> 00:37:58,563
we were able to save everyone.

428
00:38:05,012 --> 00:38:06,236
No.

429
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:12,576
We saved them because everyone was here.

430
00:38:16,839 --> 00:38:18,389
Even if...

431
00:38:18,935 --> 00:38:21,429
my vision never comes back...

432
00:38:23,365 --> 00:38:24,979
Even if I can't hold a scalpel...

433
00:38:27,876 --> 00:38:29,483
I want to stay here

434
00:38:30,229 --> 00:38:32,289
and do what I can.

435
00:38:35,366 --> 00:38:36,769
Here,

436
00:38:38,873 --> 00:38:40,936
I want to save lives together with everyone.

437
00:38:55,860 --> 00:38:57,449
Dr. Anno.

438
00:39:05,033 --> 00:39:06,536
Sorry to keep you waiting.

439
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:09,640
Your surgery...

440
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,506
I'm leaving it to Naomi.

441
00:39:15,576 --> 00:39:17,979
For the optic nerve decompression,

442
00:39:18,249 --> 00:39:22,435
I reached out to Dr. Sasao at Nagoya Medical
University, who has extensive experience.

443
00:39:24,030 --> 00:39:26,970
He can't operate due
to a scheduled surgery, but...

444
00:39:27,556 --> 00:39:29,216
He gave Naomi

445
00:39:30,163 --> 00:39:33,143
detailed instructions on the procedure.

446
00:39:37,069 --> 00:39:39,236
I can't guarantee success.

447
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:42,029
To be honest,

448
00:39:43,580 --> 00:39:45,449
I'm scared.

449
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:48,586
But...

450
00:39:49,940 --> 00:39:51,830
I'll give it everything I have.

451
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:01,403
Because I want to save you.

452
00:40:13,412 --> 00:40:14,716
I'm counting on you.

453
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:26,630
I'll need everyone's help, too.

454
00:40:26,856 --> 00:40:28,200
Yes!

455
00:40:37,436 --> 00:40:40,683
A neurosurgical approach tends
to leave visible scarring.

456
00:40:41,097 --> 00:40:43,850
So this time,
we'll use a transnasal endoscope.

457
00:40:43,850 --> 00:40:46,150
Other cranial nerves are nearby,
so be careful.

458
00:40:46,190 --> 00:40:48,821
Dr. Anno's sphenoid sinus is narrow.

459
00:40:48,821 --> 00:40:50,867
Bleeding will obscure
the visual field, so prepare

460
00:40:50,867 --> 00:40:51,990
extra irrigation fluid.

461
00:40:51,990 --> 00:40:55,108
Why the nasal route
instead of the orbital route?

462
00:40:55,108 --> 00:40:57,308
This method is less invasive.

463
00:40:57,308 --> 00:40:58,570
Through the sphenoid sinus...

464
00:40:58,570 --> 00:41:00,570
I'll handle the endoscope.

465
00:41:06,623 --> 00:41:08,116
Nervous?

466
00:41:12,282 --> 00:41:13,616
You're one to talk.

467
00:41:22,656 --> 00:41:23,856
Well then,

468
00:41:23,990 --> 00:41:25,616
shall we head to the OR?

469
00:42:13,411 --> 00:42:14,690
We will now begin

470
00:42:14,857 --> 00:42:19,837
a right optic nerve decompression surgery
on Dr. Shura Anno.

471
00:42:20,022 --> 00:42:21,589
Understood!

472
00:42:46,476 --> 00:42:48,870
Due to sudden chest pain...

473
00:42:54,456 --> 00:42:56,460
Taishaku Emergency Department.

474
00:42:56,460 --> 00:42:58,460
Female, 30s, in shock.

475
00:42:58,460 --> 00:42:59,600
We can accept her.

476
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:00,970
Please transport her now.

477
00:43:04,180 --> 00:43:05,743
Stretcher coming in!

478
00:43:08,749 --> 00:43:12,603
Regarding the opening
of the International Taishaku Hospital

479
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,080
Step back.

480
00:43:19,043 --> 00:43:20,309
Excuse me.

481
00:43:21,070 --> 00:43:22,541
Good, heartbeat's back!

482
00:43:22,541 --> 00:43:23,622
Hook up the transfusion.

483
00:43:23,622 --> 00:43:25,115
- Got it.
- Starting noradrenaline.

484
00:43:25,115 --> 00:43:27,069
- Intubating.
- Got it.

485
00:43:27,069 --> 00:43:29,949
The wound's deep. I'll irrigate and suture.

486
00:43:30,610 --> 00:43:33,277
Intra-abdominal bleeding.
Laparotomy for hemostasis.

487
00:43:33,430 --> 00:43:35,643
Doctor, no ORs are available.

488
00:43:39,140 --> 00:43:40,790
The patient is on death's door.

489
00:43:41,286 --> 00:43:43,120
We operate here. Get ready now.

490
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:44,490
Understood!
